Source: Supplied"Hyatt House Johannesburg Rosebank is everything the name represents – a welcoming and warm environment that encourages guests to live like residents. We want each and every guest who comes through our doors to feel that they can let their real-life routines roll on, even when they’re on the road," says Asif Raza, cluster general manager: Hyatt SA. "Whether guests are visiting for a short trip or an extended stay, we know Hyatt House Johannesburg Rosebank is the perfect place to offer a personalised hotel experience that will make people feel right at home."Hyatt House hotels’ apartment-style living is ideal for guests who are looking to continue their work and personal routines, helping business and leisure travellers feel at home. Source: SuppliedThe hotel offers 80 guestrooms, including 49 studio guestrooms and 31 apartment-style Kitchen Suites with fully equipped kitchens, comfy living rooms, spacious bedrooms, and stylish bathrooms; complimentary Wi-Fi throughout the hotel, guestrooms and suites; The H BAR, located alongside the pool deck and features the Sip + Snack Menu; pool deck with skyline views of Johannesburg and 24-hour gym. "In addition to the recent opening of Hyatt House Johannesburg Sandton, the opening of Hyatt House Johannesburg Rosebank is another significant milestone in South Africa’s recovering and re-emerging hospitality and tourism sector," says Hamza Farooqui, chief executive officer of Millat Investments. "With accessible flights now available from key markets, and the rising demand for extended stay travel, the stunning Hyatt House Johannesburg Rosebank will be a warmly received home-away-from-home for travellers looking to experience the best of South Africa."